summary: A frog character teaches another frog character a math riddle. The first frog asks what you call a man without a body and a nose, and the answer is "no body nose." Then, the first frog asks why 10+10 equals 11+11, and explains that 10+10 is twenty, while 11+11 is twenty-two.
transcript: What do you call a man without a body and a nose? What do you call it? No body nose. A man without a body and a nose. No body nose. Why does 10+10 equal 11+11? Why? Because 10+10 is twenty and 11+11 is twenty two.
